{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c95886d7-c11d-4737-84ec-e8895b946bb2","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit.net 2.9.3 project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n**1. Remove the old runner:**\n```xml\n<!-- Remove this package reference -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n```\n\n**2. Add the new runner:**\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n```\n\n**3. Enable the platform** in your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <UseMicrosoftTestingPlatform>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatform>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**4. Run tests** with:\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\nOr run the test project directly as an executable (Microsoft.Testing.Platform builds tests as self-contained apps):\n```bash\ndotnet run --project YourTests.csproj -- --help\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n- Your test project becomes a standalone executable\n- CLI flags change (e.g., `--filter` → `--treenode-filter`)\n- `dotnet test` still works but routes through the new platform\n- No `Program.cs` or entry point needed — the runner package handles it\n\nThat's the minimal migration. Your existing `[Fact]`/`[Theory]` tests require no changes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"aa999cad-15a8-4dc7-adf7-91b21d412eb9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration.","outputTokens":389,"requestId":"7C22:9A1BB:26D0ECD:2AD38DF:69F93E1D"},"id":"0a7c8e33-02f2-4dfd-b511-7098695a3b16","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:47:35.881Z","parentId":"3e156c82-d2bc-4285-a789-251e89f8ac2f"}
